The paper deals with dynamic graph algorithms, specifically the maintenance of reachability and distance queries under changes to the graph. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL), but more specifically, the techniques used involve logic and descriptive complexity (cs.LO) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses some preliminary results towards showing that distances are in DynFO, which could potentially fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
